      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You're right, a sudden jump in labor costs can be devastating for small businesses, especially in rural areas where the economy is already fragile. The fact is, the cost of living in many rural areas is already lower, so the burden of a minimum wage hike will disproportionately affect small businesses that are barely scraping by. It's a classic case of the government imposing a policy that will ultimately harm the very people they're trying to help.",
